  Let <fr:tex>D</fr:tex> be an <fr:link
href="axt-001S.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001S">algebraic dcpo</fr:link> and <fr:tex>U  \subseteq  D</fr:tex> a Scott open
  subset. We then have
  <fr:tex
display="block">U =  \bigcup   \{   { \uparrow } c   \mid  c  \in  U, c \  \mathsf {compact}  \} .</fr:tex></fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1031</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:source-path>/Users/ayberkt/Code/mathematical-forest/trees/public/axt-002K.tree</fr:source-path><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>10</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:parent>axt-002K</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p><fr:tex>( \impliedby )</fr:tex> This direction follows directly from the <fr:link
href="axt-001Z.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001Z">upward
    closure</fr:link> of <fr:tex>U</fr:tex>, which is entailed by its <fr:link
href="axt-001Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001Y">Scott
    openness</fr:link>.
  </fr:p>
  <fr:p><fr:tex>( \implies )</fr:tex> Let <fr:tex>x  \in  U</fr:tex>. We need to show that there exists a compact
    <fr:tex>c  \in  U</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>x  \in   { \uparrow } c</fr:tex>. Thanks to the
    <fr:link
href="axt-001S.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001S">algebraicity</fr:link> of <fr:tex>D</fr:tex>, we know that
    <fr:tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }  \{  c  \in   \mathcal {K} (D)  \mid  c  \sqsubseteq  x  \} .</fr:tex>
    The fact that <fr:tex>U</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="axt-001Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-001Y">Scott open</fr:link> entails it is inaccessible by
    directed joins so the fact that
    <fr:tex
display="block">\left ( \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }  \{  c  \in   \mathcal {K} (D)  \mid  c  \sqsubseteq  x  \} \right )  \in  U</fr:tex>
    means there exists a compact <fr:tex>c_0  \in  U</fr:tex> with <fr:tex>c_0  \sqsubseteq  x</fr:tex>
    which is to say <fr:tex>x  \in   { \uparrow } c_0</fr:tex>.
  </fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
